00:30:42,824 --> 00:30:44,959
Why do you think
they called you back?

271
00:30:44,993 --> 00:30:47,195
What's happening?

272
00:30:47,229 --> 00:30:49,230
Gotta take care of your partner.

273
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:52,733
How am I supposed
to take care of my partner

274
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:54,602
if nobody tells me
what's going on, man?

275
00:30:54,636 --> 00:30:56,270
He's cracked
all the biggies.

276
00:30:56,305 --> 00:30:58,105
This one's cracking him.

277
00:30:59,341 --> 00:31:01,275
You didn't get them from me.

278
00:31:05,113 --> 00:31:07,048
Detective Vega,
Homicide.

279
00:31:11,353 --> 00:31:13,654
Suit up, Taylor.
We got another body.

280
00:31:15,023 --> 00:31:16,557
Later, Perez.

281
00:31:16,592 --> 00:31:18,226
Later.

282
00:31:24,933 --> 00:31:28,336
"Ms. Yates described
hearing voices."

283
00:31:35,978 --> 00:31:37,411
Mrs. Harwich,
why did you have

284
00:31:37,446 --> 00:31:39,113
to drown your daughter?

285
00:31:39,147 --> 00:31:41,349
I want to make them cry.

286
00:31:41,383 --> 00:31:43,384
Cry...
Make them cry.

287
00:31:46,455 --> 00:31:49,390
"Todd Scott, a 4-year-old boy,
was found dead in his apartment

288
00:31:49,424 --> 00:31:54,562
by his father, Alex Scott,
a Wall Street financial analyst.

289
00:31:54,596 --> 00:31:56,998
Lisa Scott, the child's mother,
is being held for questioning."

290
00:31:59,468 --> 00:32:01,536
Holy shit.

291
00:32:06,575 --> 00:32:08,709
I know you.

292
00:32:08,744 --> 00:32:11,946
You're like me.

293
00:32:11,980 --> 00:32:14,749
You want what I want.

294
00:32:15,951 --> 00:32:17,518
Alex.

295
00:32:19,054 --> 00:32:22,223
I hear you crying.

296
00:32:22,257 --> 00:32:24,025
You can't stop me.

297
00:32:24,059 --> 00:32:25,760
Answer me!

298
00:32:29,198 --> 00:32:31,532
Make it stop.

299
00:32:56,291 --> 00:32:57,358
Where we going?

300
00:32:57,392 --> 00:32:58,826
See a friend.

301
00:33:06,435 --> 00:33:08,236
Don't worry, baby.

302
00:33:08,270 --> 00:33:09,971
It's gonna be OK.

303
00:34:12,067 --> 00:34:13,434
That's bullshit.

304
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,269
Look, man, this isn't procedure.
I gotta be there.

305
00:34:15,304 --> 00:34:16,470
It's personal.

306
00:34:16,505 --> 00:34:17,872
What isn't?

307
00:34:17,906 --> 00:34:19,173
I don't want to
get into it.

308
00:34:19,208 --> 00:34:20,641
You got to get into
something sometime.

309
00:34:20,676 --> 00:34:22,109
Look...

310
00:34:22,144 --> 00:34:24,178
I'm gonna see him myself, OK?

311
00:34:26,815 --> 00:34:29,517
Fuck it.
I gotta find a bathroom anyway.

312
00:34:33,388 --> 00:34:36,257
What's it been?
Seven...eight years?

313
00:34:36,291 --> 00:34:37,792
Eight.

314
00:34:38,827 --> 00:34:40,661
So why now?

315
00:34:46,468 --> 00:34:49,470
Today...

316
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:52,306
a woman killed her kid.

317
00:34:54,109 --> 00:34:56,444
She said Rachel knows.

318
00:35:00,549 --> 00:35:05,686
There was this...
these voices....

319
00:35:05,721 --> 00:35:08,523
this crying.

320
00:35:11,894 --> 00:35:13,561
I just think they may
have something to do

321
00:35:13,595 --> 00:35:15,696
with the missing kids.

322
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:21,435
You still haven't forgiven
yourself, have you?

323
00:35:23,872 --> 00:35:26,774
Todd was my son.

324
00:35:26,808 --> 00:35:28,910
And Lisa was his mother.

325
00:35:28,944 --> 00:35:30,745
How could you know?

326
00:35:34,116 --> 00:35:35,950
Rachel cries,

327
00:35:35,984 --> 00:35:38,386
like any mother
who loses her child.

328
00:35:38,420 --> 00:35:41,989
Like Lisa did after
she took Todd's life,

329
00:35:42,024 --> 00:35:44,292
and before she took her own.

330
00:35:49,031 --> 00:35:51,632
You know what's
going on, don't you?

331
00:35:54,102 --> 00:35:55,937
It's simple.

332
00:35:55,971 --> 00:35:59,407
Your demons are
staring you in the face.

333
00:35:59,441 --> 00:36:02,310
What are you
going to do, Alex?

334
00:36:08,517 --> 00:36:11,052
I want you to see
a friend of mine.

335
00:36:11,086 --> 00:36:12,620
She knows things.

336
00:36:12,654 --> 00:36:14,155
Knows things?

337
00:36:14,189 --> 00:36:16,324
Things the Church condemns.

338
00:36:16,358 --> 00:36:18,426
Ask her about La Llorona.

339
00:36:18,460 --> 00:36:20,161
What's that?

340
00:36:20,195 --> 00:36:21,896
The answer.

341
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:27,468
Fear...

342
00:36:27,503 --> 00:36:29,871
It's everywhere.

343
00:36:29,905 --> 00:36:32,907
You can smell it
in the streets.

344
00:36:34,276 --> 00:36:35,810
We got a floater.

345
00:36:35,844 --> 00:36:37,144
Father.

346
00:36:39,114 --> 00:36:40,681
You still have that
medal I gave you

347
00:36:40,716 --> 00:36:43,050
when you made your
First Communion?

348
00:36:46,188 --> 00:36:49,190
Saint Michael, Archangel,
defend us in battle.

349
00:36:51,593 --> 00:36:53,394
Thank you, Father.

350
00:36:58,133 --> 00:37:02,336
And thrust into Hell,
Satan and the evil spirits

351
00:37:02,371 --> 00:37:05,373
who prowl the world
for the ruin of souls.

352
00:37:08,844 --> 00:37:10,678
(Father)
Amen.

353
00:37:13,182 --> 00:37:14,715
Don't worry, baby.

354
00:37:14,750 --> 00:37:16,350
We're almost there.

355
00:37:35,204 --> 00:37:36,871
You did this.

356
00:37:39,274 --> 00:37:40,875
You don't want to help me.

357
00:37:40,909 --> 00:37:42,677
You're with her.

358
00:38:06,602 --> 00:38:08,736
You ever heard
of La Loreena?

359
00:38:08,770 --> 00:38:10,004
La what?

360
00:38:10,038 --> 00:38:12,406
I don't know.
It's like, La Lorena.

361
00:38:12,441 --> 00:38:15,076
La Yoh-roh-na.
Yeah, I heard of her.

362
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:16,544
These Mexican kids
where I grew up,

363
00:38:16,578 --> 00:38:18,179
they were obsessed with her.

364
00:38:18,213 --> 00:38:19,547
Her?

365
00:38:19,581 --> 00:38:21,749
Yeah.
The crying woman.

366
00:38:21,783 --> 00:38:23,317
La Llorona.

367
00:38:23,352 --> 00:38:25,653
Yeah, well what's her story?

368
00:38:25,687 --> 00:38:28,089
Some guy cheated on her,
or something like that.

369
00:38:28,123 --> 00:38:32,293
So she lost it and then...

370
00:38:32,327 --> 00:38:34,028
And then what?

371
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:36,130
She drowned her kids.

372
00:38:36,164 --> 00:38:39,000
Because of that
she was cursed forever.

373
00:38:39,034 --> 00:38:41,302
You know these
Mexicans, man.

374
00:38:41,336 --> 00:38:44,205
Their parents used to
scare the shit of us.

375
00:38:44,239 --> 00:38:45,473
They used to say stuff like,

376
00:38:45,507 --> 00:38:47,875
"Don't go by the river
or she'll get you."

377
00:38:55,951 --> 00:38:57,952
I don't get it.
What is she?

378
00:38:59,621 --> 00:39:01,556
One angry bitch.

379
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:03,791
That's what she is.

380
00:39:17,940 --> 00:39:19,574
I saw your name
on the ops order.

381
00:39:19,608 --> 00:39:21,042
Thought you might
want a first look.

382
00:39:21,076 --> 00:39:22,376
All right, so what
are we looking at?

383
00:39:22,411 --> 00:39:24,445
Some guy walking
his dog found it.

384
00:39:24,479 --> 00:39:28,082
The good news is the fish
population is back.

385
00:39:28,116 --> 00:39:31,586
The bad news,
there's not much left.

386
00:39:32,487 --> 00:39:34,655
Perez, I hope you
have an iron stomach.

387
00:39:55,944 --> 00:39:57,278
Jesus Christ.

388
00:39:57,312 --> 00:39:59,313
Can't be more than
9 or 10 years old.

389
00:40:02,551 --> 00:40:04,552
[whisper]
<i>He misses you.</i>

390
00:40:22,471 --> 00:40:23,638
[phone rings]

391
00:40:24,706 --> 00:40:26,607
What do you think?

392
00:40:28,177 --> 00:40:29,777
Hey, Scott.

393
00:40:29,811 --> 00:40:31,212
What?

394
00:40:32,181 --> 00:40:33,814
You all right?

395
00:40:34,816 --> 00:40:36,317
Yeah.
I'm cool.

396
00:40:36,952 --> 00:40:38,586
Is it yours?

397
00:40:38,620 --> 00:40:39,687
Mine?

398
00:40:39,721 --> 00:40:41,722
One of your MIAs?

399
00:40:44,193 --> 00:40:46,127
Hard to tell.

400
00:40:47,396 --> 00:40:49,564
It was a boy.

401
00:40:50,465 --> 00:40:51,699
Look.

402
00:40:51,733 --> 00:40:54,135
Looks like some kind
of braided branch?

403
00:40:57,339 --> 00:40:59,640
Bag it for evidence.

404
00:40:59,675 --> 00:41:02,410
Have them canvas the river
a quarter-mile down.

405
00:41:02,444 --> 00:41:04,912
And tell the M.E.
I want DNA yesterday.

406
00:41:04,947 --> 00:41:06,581
You got it.

407
00:41:10,219 --> 00:41:11,519
<i>Daddy...</i>

408
00:41:12,821 --> 00:41:14,722
Daddy!

409
00:41:15,724 --> 00:41:17,425
Making breakfast.

410
00:41:19,561 --> 00:41:22,063
Yeah.
Ice cream with fudge sauce.

411
00:41:23,332 --> 00:41:25,233
She's asleep.

412
00:41:29,004 --> 00:41:30,938
Mommy.

413
00:41:31,740 --> 00:41:33,341
Mommy.

414
00:41:34,910 --> 00:41:36,644
It's Daddy.

415
00:41:36,678 --> 00:41:38,346
Mommy!

416
00:41:43,118 --> 00:41:44,852
Hey, Wall Street.

417
00:41:44,887 --> 00:41:46,854
Take care of yourself.

418
00:41:49,057 --> 00:41:50,658
Wall Street?

419
00:41:50,692 --> 00:41:52,660
Life before Owens.

420
00:41:52,694 --> 00:41:54,362
We gotta make a stop.

421
00:41:57,032 --> 00:42:00,568
What's this, man?
First a priest, now a curandera?

422
00:42:00,602 --> 00:42:02,270
A curandera?
What's that?

423
00:42:02,304 --> 00:42:03,905
She's like a witch.

424
00:42:03,939 --> 00:42:04,972
Let me guess.

425
00:42:05,007 --> 00:42:07,842
Witches make
your stomach upset.

426
00:42:34,369 --> 00:42:35,670
Tonio.

427
00:42:45,647 --> 00:42:46,881
Tonio.

428
00:43:33,328 --> 00:43:35,129
[phone rings]

429
00:43:35,163 --> 00:43:37,431
Scott, Homicide.
Leave a message.

430
00:43:38,167 --> 00:43:40,334
Detective Scott.

431
00:43:40,369 --> 00:43:42,770
Meet us at the park.
The angel.

432
00:44:16,672 --> 00:44:19,740
You know, this morning,
in the interrogation room.

433
00:44:19,775 --> 00:44:21,909
There was something strange
going on, don't you think?

434
00:44:23,212 --> 00:44:26,214
Like, you guys knew
each other already,

435
00:44:26,248 --> 00:44:28,249
or you knew something like her.

436
00:44:34,256 --> 00:44:36,924
You know what?
Now that I think about it,

437
00:44:36,959 --> 00:44:39,927
she reminds me of my mother.

438
00:44:39,962 --> 00:44:41,062
Those eyes.

439
00:44:41,096 --> 00:44:42,930
And that voice.

440
00:44:42,965 --> 00:44:44,098
Jesus.

441
00:44:44,132 --> 00:44:46,801
You know my mom.
What do you think?

442
00:44:48,704 --> 00:44:51,172
I think we should
cut down Broadway.

443
00:44:58,447 --> 00:45:01,148
Yeah.
It's probably faster.

444
00:45:22,004 --> 00:45:23,638
Hey.

445
00:45:23,672 --> 00:45:25,640
I know.

446
00:45:25,674 --> 00:45:27,808
Know what?

447
00:45:27,843 --> 00:45:30,178
About you and your kid.

448
00:45:30,812 --> 00:45:32,947
We're partners, man.

449
00:45:35,951 --> 00:45:38,085
You know, this morning,
when that reporter asked us

450
00:45:38,120 --> 00:45:40,988
why would a woman
kill her own kid?

451
00:45:43,058 --> 00:45:45,693
All that shit
they must go through.

452
00:45:45,727 --> 00:45:47,228
Every breath they
take must feel like

453
00:45:47,262 --> 00:45:49,630
a razor slashing
into their guts.

454
00:45:49,665 --> 00:45:52,166
Maybe they're just
trying to breathe.

455
00:45:54,436 --> 00:45:56,003
And you?

456
00:45:56,038 --> 00:45:58,439
Are you trying to breathe?

457
00:45:59,374 --> 00:46:01,709
Dead people don't breathe.

458
00:46:48,957 --> 00:46:50,358
After you.

459
00:46:59,868 --> 00:47:04,872
[La Llorona whispers]

460
00:47:24,359 --> 00:47:28,129
[conversation in Spanish]

461
00:47:34,736 --> 00:47:36,304
What'd she say?

462
00:47:36,338 --> 00:47:38,639
She wants to know
what took us so long.

463
00:47:38,674 --> 00:47:40,474
Sit down.

464
00:47:54,089 --> 00:47:55,990
Padre Joe sent me.

465
00:47:56,024 --> 00:47:57,959
Amigo.

466
00:47:59,094 --> 00:48:00,761
Si.

467
00:48:00,796 --> 00:48:02,797
Amigo.

468
00:48:03,565 --> 00:48:06,033
Tienes problemas, hijo?

469
00:48:07,236 --> 00:48:09,637
Muchos problemas.

470
00:48:12,074 --> 00:48:13,774
Show her.

471
00:48:21,316 --> 00:48:23,084
Mira.

472
00:48:28,390 --> 00:48:30,191
Is that witchcraft?

473
00:48:30,225 --> 00:48:31,626
Es brujeria?

474
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:39,934
No.

475
00:48:39,968 --> 00:48:42,003
Eso no es brujeria.

476
00:48:45,240 --> 00:48:48,009
[continues speaking Spanish]

477
00:48:51,947 --> 00:48:53,714
She said
stop bullshitting her

478
00:48:53,749 --> 00:48:55,816
and ask what you
came here to ask her.

479
00:49:00,556 --> 00:49:02,790
La Llorona.

480
00:49:03,358 --> 00:49:05,626
Ahhh...

481
00:49:05,661 --> 00:49:07,929
La Llorona.

482
00:49:09,031 --> 00:49:10,932
What do you--

483
00:49:10,966 --> 00:49:12,500
What does she know?

484
00:49:13,602 --> 00:49:15,837
[interpreting]

485
00:49:31,653 --> 00:49:34,188
La Llorona is a force who
carries the deepest pain

486
00:49:34,223 --> 00:49:36,924
and most vicious rage
that ever existed...

487
00:49:39,027 --> 00:49:40,828
In all eternity.

488
00:49:46,168 --> 00:49:48,369
The Greek Medea,
the Jewish Lilith...

489
00:49:54,376 --> 00:49:57,345
The Aztec Malinche,
Lamia, also Greek.

490
00:50:00,749 --> 00:50:02,917
The Crying Winds from Africa.

491
00:50:06,021 --> 00:50:07,688
Rachel of Rama.

492
00:50:12,127 --> 00:50:13,961
She takes on many shapes.

493
00:50:13,996 --> 00:50:15,830
What shapes?

494
00:50:24,806 --> 00:50:27,341
She's like the Virgin Mary,
looking for her kid...

495
00:50:27,376 --> 00:50:29,177
the only one that
can stop her pain.

496
00:50:39,555 --> 00:50:42,223
She's a siren getting
revenge against men

497
00:50:42,257 --> 00:50:43,858
that take advantage of women.

498
00:50:43,892 --> 00:50:47,028
Men like the one
that betrayed her.

499
00:50:59,808 --> 00:51:02,543
She's the monster that
puts the evil eye on mothers

500
00:51:02,578 --> 00:51:05,279
because she wants to be
in the company of misery -

501
00:51:05,314 --> 00:51:08,182
with other Lloronas like her.

502
00:51:19,595 --> 00:51:24,499
Like Death,
La Llorona is everywhere.

503
00:51:24,533 --> 00:51:28,936
In all places, at all times.

504
00:51:30,906 --> 00:51:34,075
Why here?
Why now?

505
00:51:34,109 --> 00:51:36,310
Uh...Por que ahora?

506
00:51:42,251 --> 00:51:44,151
Her kid is here.

507
00:51:44,186 --> 00:51:45,853
She's looking for him.

508
00:51:46,255 --> 00:51:47,722
Her kid?

509
00:51:51,059 --> 00:51:52,827
Reincarnated.

510
00:51:55,764 --> 00:51:58,266
<i>For 500 years I've cried...</i>

511
00:52:07,543 --> 00:52:09,977
How do we stop her?

512
00:52:22,391 --> 00:52:24,859
The mothers
that see her face,

513
00:52:24,893 --> 00:52:27,228
the face of the monster -

514
00:52:27,262 --> 00:52:30,731
they need to take out
the evil eye.

515
00:52:32,434 --> 00:52:33,935
Agua.

516
00:52:35,637 --> 00:52:38,072
She gets her power
from water.

517
00:52:41,143 --> 00:52:43,244
What about the children?

518
00:52:43,278 --> 00:52:45,112
Los ninos?

519
00:52:51,220 --> 00:52:55,089
Close to the mother's heart,
La Llorona can't take them.

520
00:53:06,502 --> 00:53:08,336
She's close.
There's not much time.

521
00:53:22,618 --> 00:53:24,785
What did she say?

522
00:53:26,855 --> 00:53:29,991
She finally found what
she was looking for -

523
00:53:30,025 --> 00:53:31,526
Her kid.

524
00:53:39,168 --> 00:53:41,202
The angel.
In the park.

525
00:53:46,074 --> 00:53:47,675
Mommy?

526
00:53:48,443 --> 00:53:50,878
<i>You abandoned him.</i>

527
00:54:00,122 --> 00:54:01,989
Daddy says to call.

528
00:54:04,026 --> 00:54:06,394
Did you open a new jar?

529
00:54:06,428 --> 00:54:08,462
Daddy said I could.

530
00:54:10,999 --> 00:54:12,800
I'm the mother.

531
00:54:14,102 --> 00:54:16,070
I'll put it back.

532
00:54:19,241 --> 00:54:21,409
It's too late.

533
00:54:32,821 --> 00:54:34,755
You're dirty.

534
00:54:34,790 --> 00:54:36,624
Go wash.

535
00:54:56,011 --> 00:54:58,112
[speaking Spanish]

536
00:55:11,260 --> 00:55:13,194
Gracias.

537
00:55:18,534 --> 00:55:20,501
<i>I give life...</i>

538
00:55:22,704 --> 00:55:25,373
<i>I take life.</i>

539
00:55:45,894 --> 00:55:50,298
<i>Maria...</i>

540
00:55:50,332 --> 00:55:53,501
<i>Walk with me.</i>

541
00:56:01,176 --> 00:56:04,846
<i>See what I see.</i>

542
00:56:16,692 --> 00:56:18,259
<i>Maria!</i>

543
00:57:16,852 --> 00:57:18,853
[screaming]

544
00:57:26,228 --> 00:57:27,728
Maria!

545
00:57:27,763 --> 00:57:29,197
Aye, Maria!

546
00:57:29,231 --> 00:57:32,133
